## 2. Fix #14 implementation — three-file minimal change

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `solver/partitioner.py` | Added `Partition.all_resources: Optional[List[Dict]]` field. `create_partitions` populates with the unfiltered team/group-filtered input. `solve_partition` stashes `preprocessed.all_plan_resource_ids` so `model.py` can pick it up. |
| `solver/checkpoint_manager.py` | `_split_oversized_partition` now forwards `partition.all_resources` to each sub-partition. Without this, sub-partitions would revert to the category-filtered list and re-introduce the gap. |
| `solver/model.py` | LC-06 invocation reads `data.all_plan_resource_ids` (falls back to `data.resource_ids`), passes it to `compute_rest_targets` and to `add_rest_days_constraints` via a new `all_resource_ids` kwarg. |
| `constraints/lc_06_rest_days_allocation.py` | Accepts optional `all_resource_ids` param. All LC-06 var-creation + constraint loops now iterate `lc06_resource_ids`. Overlap constraints naturally auto-filter via the existing `if x_key not in x_vars: continue` check — no new guards needed. New log line summarizes scope expansion. |

**Signature backward-compat**: `add_rest_days_constraints` still returns `(rt_vars, ct_vars, violations, metadata)`. Only caller is model.py, already updated.

**Team-filter preserved**: `all_resources` is whatever `service.py` passed to the partitioner — which is already team-filtered by the payload's `target_team_ids`. The fix bypasses ONLY the category filter, NOT the team filter.

**Gated on CT/RT replanning**: if `rt_replannable=False AND ct_replannable=False`, the entire LC-06 block is skipped. T-BASE runs behave identically to pre-Fix-#14.

